          "id": 1,
          "name": "Advice and Information about Asylum and Refugee Services",
          "description": "<p><span><b>Due to the coronavirus COVID-19 pandemic, many services are either closed or running very reduced services and most activities are cancelled.&#160; This is includes the Wednesday afternoon drop in at Victoria Hall and The Sanctuary on Chapel Walk.&#160; Please see Printable Resources for details of the services currently available to refugees and asylum seekers in Sheffield.</b></span><br></p><p><span><b>Citizens' Advice Sheffield are operating phone advice services only - see Providers for detauls.</b></span></p><p><b>Migrant Help</b>&#160;operate a free phone line and e-mail service which can give advice and support on a variety of issues. They can also offer a 'face to face' service for vulnerable clients which will take place within 30 minutes travel time for the client if they are in dispersed accommodation, the vulnerable client referral form is in printable resources. See provider details for contact details and scope of service.&#8203; There are information letters in printable resources about Migrant Help translated into a variety of languages.</p><p>The <a href=\"http://righttoremain.org.uk/toolkit\" target=\"_blank\">Right to Remain toolkit</a> has information about the asylum and immigration system.&#160; The following sections of the toolkit have been translated into&#160;<span>Arabic, Farsi, Pashto, Tigrinya, Amh</span>aric and French:-</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://righttoremain.org.uk/toolkit/asylumintro.html\" target=\"_blank\">What is asylum?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://righttoremain.org.uk/toolkit/screening.html\" target=\"_blank\">Asylum screening interview</a><br></li><li><a href=\"https://righttoremain.org.uk/toolkit/asylumiv.html\" target=\"_blank\">Asylum Substantive Interview</a></li><li><a href=\"https://righttoremain.org.uk/toolkit/refusal.html\" target=\"_blank\">After a Refusal</a></li></ul><p>This<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cqaW_6uUXnQ&amp;t=1s&amp;fbclid=IwAR1bzMw3vDje5L4mGK5JZK_OI9fBOMUKkMdZI_tVKc0hKRSHnd__WxL_K0M\" target=\"_blank\"> You Tube video</a> explains how to use this Toolkit.</p><p>The Citizen's Advice Bureau has a site giving advice about immigration issues <a href=\"https://www.citizensadvice.org.uk/immigration/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">here</a>&#160;- see Printable Resources for their locations and opening times.</p><p>The Refugee Council have produced an <a href=\"http://refugeecouncil.org.uk/assets/0003/6009/Information_pack_for_refugees_Oct_2015.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Information Pack</a> for refugees&#160;</p>",
