                      "name": "Wednesday Multi-Agency Drop In",
                      "description": "<p>A one stop drop-in service runs every Wednesday afternoon from 1pm to 4pm at the Victoria Hall in Sheffield city centre.  A range of services are present including Assist, Red Cross, Migrant Help, City of Sanctuary, Snowdrop Project.  They will try to answer questions about services, provide information, help and signposting.  Interpreters are present, but there is no guarantee that a interpreter for a particular language will be available.  A conversation club is run at the same time. See printable resources for a list of monthly attendees.</p>",
