                      "id": 444,
                      "name": "Migrant Help",
                      "description": "<p>Migrant Help offers support, guidance and accommodation to vulnerable migrants across the UK.&#160;  They provide help on completing asylum support application (section 95 / section 4 / a change of circumstance); advice on financial support, S4 Appeals, finding legal representation, the asylum process, accessing primary health care, initial accommodation, housing complaints and EST.&#160;</p><p>Helpline (free from landlines and mobiles in 15 languages): 0808 8010 503. E-mail: ah@migranthelp.org.uk.</p><p>In addition, Migrant Help have introduced a new web chat facility which is especially useful if the phone line in busy. Just click on<b>&#160;</b>Contact Us on the Service User Portal:&#160;<a href=\"http://www.migranthelpuk.org/su-portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">www.migranthelpuk.org/su-portal</a><br><br></p>",
