                      "id": 1044,
                      "name": "New Beginnings Project",
                      "description": "<p><b>Coronavirus update:&#160; The office is closed.&#160; Please contact them by phone or email.</b></p><p><br></p><p>This Project is part of Voluntary Action Sheffield (VAS).  It helps Refugees and Asylum Seekers to access support and information on education, volunteering and employment opportunities.We are based in Sheffield City Centre, just off Division Street (behind Costa Coffee). See MapIf you are an asylum seeker or refugee, we can help you to get actively involved and contribute to mainstream life in Sheffield througheducationvolunteering andemployment supportOur Service provides one to one support to people looking to build skills and knowledge, meet new people, improve English and secure Employment.Come and speak to us and find out how we can help you. Appointments are available throughout the week Please call us on <a href=\"tel:01142536655\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">0114 2536655</a>- See more at: <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldvolunteercentre.org.uk/new-beginnings-project#sthash.DMMwdwwb.dpuf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">sheffieldvolunteercentre.org.uk/new-beginnings-project#sthash.DMMwdwwb.dpuf</a></p>",
