          "id": 2,
          "name": "Support on Arrival in Sheffield",
          "description": "<p>Asylum seekers who are being supported by the Home Office after they have made their asylum claim will be brought ( usually from Urban House in Wakefield) by <b>Mears</b>&#160;to  an allocated property in Sheffield.&#160;</p><p>Mears hold the contract for providing accommodation for asylum seekers in Sheffield until September 2029.  They are responsible for introducing people to the city, providing subsistence money and helping them settle in.  They provide 'welcome' information in a pack.&#160;</p><p>For families with school age children, Mears should inform the City Council that the children need school places.&#160;</p><p>New asylum seekers are taken to the <b>Mulberry Health Practice</b> to register with a GP, usually on Wednesday mornings.&#160;</p><p>&#160;<b>City of Sanctuary Sheffield </b>runs a Welcome Project: volunteers meet new asylum seekers at the Mulberry Health practice, and welcome them to the city with the offer of a cup of tea and a biscuit.  They also introduce people to the Wednesday afternoon drop-in and tell them how to find help and support in the city.</p>",
