          "id": 10,
          "name": "Housing for Asylum Seekers Awaiting a Decision",
          "description": "<p><b>Mears Group</b> hold the contract from the Home Office for providing accommodation for families and single people.  They  bring people from Urban House in Wakefield to Sheffield to their new accommodation.</p><p>Mears<span>&#160;have 9 working days to allocate accommodation.People can ask for a change in accommodation. Mears will consider requests to move house if the accommodation is unsuitable e.g. a change to family size, emergency repair, Home Office request.  However, there is no guarantee that people asking to change accommodation will be re-housed in Sheffield or nearby.</span></p><p></p><p>Repairs and complaints can be reported through <b>Migrant Help</b>'s freephone telephone number, details in provider resources. Details about accommodation standards can be found in printable resources, as well as details of helpline service standards.</p><p></p><p><span><b>Shelter</b> can offer advice and support on housing issues.  The Council's<b> Environmental Health </b>department may also be involved&#160; if there are environmental health or safeguarding issues with the accommodation.</span></p><p></p><p><b>SYMAAG</b>&#160;will offer campaigning support for those concerned about the quality or suitability of their accommodation.</p><p></p>",
