          "description": "<p><b>Sheffield Libraries</b> offer free internet access, and use of computers.  You usually need to book a slot to use one of their computers.  There is a small charge for print outs or photocopies.  See <a href=\"https://www.sheffield.gov.uk/home/libraries-archives/our-libraries\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">here</a>&#160;for locations and opening times.&#160; Details of the computer services available are <a href=\"https://www.sheffield.gov.uk/home/libraries-archives/computer-help-support\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></p><p><b>The Sanctuary</b> offers free access to computers and free WiFi.&#160; It is open 10am to 4pm, Monday to Thursday.&#160; The address is 37-39 Chapel Walk S1 2PD .</p><p>Sheffield Free Wifi is available in&#160;</p><ul><li>the&#160;Theatre District/Retail Zone, including Fargate, The Moor, Tudor Square, Peace Gardens, and Pinstone Street</li><li>the Entertainment Zone, featuring West Street, Division Street and Wellington Street&#160;</li><li>the Arrivals Zone, which covers the areas around the city centre&#8217;s main transport exchanges</li><li>&#160;the Cultural Industries and Devonshire Quarter,</li></ul><p><span>Also see<i> </i></span><a href=\"https://asylumjourney.org.uk/service/691\" target=\"\"><i>IT Skills Trainin</i></a><i>g </i><span>for help in using computers and the internet</span><br></p><p><br></p>",
