          "id": 56,
          "name": "Sports and Fitness",
          "description": "<p><span>There are many free and / or low cost sports and fitness activities listed below.&#160; Also see the Sports and Fitness leaflet in&#160; Printable Resources which includes many of these.&#160; All free for asylum seekers unless stated otherwise.</span><br></p><p></p><p></p><p><i><b></b></i></p><p><b>FOOTBALL</b><br></p><p></p><ul><li><b>Belonging Together</b>&#160;weekly football session for refugees and asylum seekers provided by&#160;<b>FURD</b>&#160;(Football Unites Racism Divides), based at the U-Mix centre. A small free lunch is included. More free and paid sessions are available, including women's football and walking football, at&#160;<a href=\"https://furd.org/public-sessions-at-the-u-mix-centre\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">furd.org/public-sessions-at-the-u-mix-centre</a></li></ul><p><b>BOXING</b><br></p><p></p><p></p><ul><li><b>Sheffield City Boxing Club</b>&#160;has free boxing sessions for asylum seekers and refugees. See poster in Printable Resources</li></ul><p></p><p></p><div><b>HEALTH WALKS</b><br></div><p></p><p></p><ul><li>F<b>r</b>ee health walks are arranged every weekday by <b>Step Out Sheffield</b> see timetable <a href=\"https://www.walkingforhealth.org.uk/walkfinder/yorkshire-and-humber/sheffield-step-out-better-lifestyle\" target=\"_blank\">here </a>.  No walk is more than 3 miles in distance and they rarely walk for more than an hour.&#160;&#160;</li></ul><p></p><div><b>RUNNING</b><br></div><p></p><p></p><ul><li>There are 6 Park Runs in Sheffield every Saturday at 9:00 which are 5kms long .  Free to enter but <a href=\"http://parkrun.org.uk/register\" target=\"_blank\">register</a> on line and print a barcode first - these are at&#160;<a href=\"http://www.parkrun.org.uk/concord\" target=\"_blank\">Concord Park</a>,&#160;<a href=\"http://www.parkrun.org.uk/sheffieldhallam\" target=\"_blank\">Endcliffe Park</a>,&#160;<a href=\"http://www.parkrun.org.uk/hillsborough\" target=\"_blank\">Hillsborough Park</a>,&#160;<a href=\"http://www.parkrun.org.uk/sheffieldcastle\" target=\"_blank\">Manor Fields Park</a>,&#160;<a href=\"http://www.parkrun.org.uk/graves\" target=\"_blank\">Graves Park</a>&#160;and&#160;<a href=\"http://www.parkrun.org.uk/rothervalley\" target=\"_blank\">Rother Valley</a>.&#160;&#160;</li><li>There are also 30 marked <a href=\"https://www.theoutdoorcity.co.uk/blog/read/2019/01/find-your-pace-with-the-outdoor-city-run-routes-b113\" target=\"\">run routes</a> in Sheffield.&#160;&#160;</li><li><b>Good Gym</b> are a community of runners that combines getting fit with doing good - see their <a href=\"https://www.goodgym.org/areas/sheffield\" target=\"_blank\">web site</a> for more details.&#160;</li></ul><p></p><div><b>CYCLING</b><br></div><p></p><p></p><ul><li>&#160;&#160;<b>COMAC</b>&#160;can provide and help maintain re-used bikes for Asylum Seekers, see their <a href=\"http://comac.org.uk/sessions/\" target=\"\">website </a>for drop in times and how to make a referral. They are up and running again after covid but have limited volunteers and workshop space, and so, the waiting list is longer than usual.</li><li><b>Recycle Bikes </b>is an  independent, not-for-profit, bike project that sells reconditioned bikes and carries out bike maintenance.</li></ul><p></p><p></p><div><b>CENTRES IN LOCAL AREAS</b><br></div><p></p><p></p><ul><li><b>Zest Centre&#160;</b>&#160;(based in Upperthorpe) has a gym, fitness classes and swimming - these are not free, but are reasonably priced.&#160;</li><li><b>Fit 4 All Gym</b> at Burton Street Hillsborough has a gym that is free for all asylum seekers to use during the day - go to the health desk at the multi agency drop in on Wednesdays between 13:00 - 16:00 in Victoria Hall to arrange an induction (this is normally available fortnightly). For non asylum seekers, there is a reasonably priced membership scheme.<br><br><br></li></ul>",
