                      "name": "The Sheffield Project for Refugee INtegration and Growth (SPRING)",
                      "description": "<p>The Sheffield Project for Refugee INtegration and Growth (SPRING) is a partnership between: City of Sanctuary, Sheffield;&#160; CAB, Sheffield; VAS; Sheffield City Council; SAVTE and SOLACE. It is funded by the EU Managing Migration Fund to co-ordinate services for Refugees.</p><p>The Spring Project can provide support&#160; with: housing issues; immigration issues; welfare benefits; learning English; volunteering opportunities; employment; counselling. &#160;&#160;</p><p>Services can be accessed by&#160;c<span>alling Blessan on 07421 313518 or via email at <a href=\"mailto:blessan@sheffield.cityofsanctuary.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">blessan@sheffield.cityofsanctuary.org</a> to make a referral.</span></p><p>Spring Project may be able to arrange a volunteer accompanier for your referral's first appointment.</p><p><br></p><p>&#160;<br></p>",
