                      "id": 824,
                      "name": "British Red Cross",
                      "description": "<p>British Red Cross provides short-term, one-to-one casework advice and support to refugees and asylum seekers to help them understand their rights and other services they can access. It provides short-term destitution support as well as pays for the travel costs for the reunion of refugee families and tracing family members.&#160; &#160;They are present at the multi-agency drop in on Wednesdays&#160;<span>1pm-4pm .&#160; They have case work appointments at The Sanctuary - these must be pre-booked.</span></p>",
