                      "id": 584,
                      "name": "Sheffield Futures",
                      "description": "Sheffield Futures provides advice for young people under 18 on employment, apprenticeships, training opportunities and/or benefits.  General drop In: Mon-Thu 9am-5pm, Fri 10am-4:30pm  \r\nSexual health drop ins are also available.  Check times of drop ins on 0114 201 2800.  \r\nCommunity Youth Teams provides 1:1 support, group work programmes, centre based and detached youth work in communities, and support for young people with alcohol and drug abuse.  Direct Line: 0800 138 8381 \r\nSexual Exploitation Service provides help for young people under 18 who may be vulnerable to sexual exploitation.  Call 0114 201 8645 or email sses@sheffieldfutures.org.uk in the strictest of confidence.",
