          "id": 621,
          "name": "Living Well in South East Sheffield",
          "description": "<p>The '<b>Your Guide to Living Well in South East Sheffield</b>' in Printable Resources is a comprehensive guide to activities and services in South East Sheffield (see * below for the areas covered). The guide includes:</p><ul><li>&#8203;sources of information, guidance and advice</li><li>family centres and childcare</li><li>local GP services (doctors)&#160;</li><li>health and wellbeing clubs,&#160; groups and services</li><li>classes and activities</li></ul><p>The main local providers are:</p><p></p><p><b>MANOR</b></p><ul><li><b>Manor and Castle Development Trust</b>&#160;run health and well being activities, a work club, activities for children and young people and offer volunteering opportunities.&#160; See their&#160;<a href=\"https://manorandcastle.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">web site</a>&#160;for more information</li><li><b>Manor Training and Resource Centre (MaTReC)&#160;</b>&#160;teach functional basic skills including English, Maths and basic ICT including supporting adults with specific learning difficulties to reach their potential to gain confidence and self esteem.&#160; See their <a href=\"https://matrec.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">web site </a>for more information.</li></ul><p><b>ARBOURTHORNE</b><br></p><ul><li><b>The Spires Centre&#160;</b>at Arbourthorne is a community centre open every day that has a number of different activities happening throughout the week, varying from youth-work to a church, and support groups for addicts to lunch clubs.&#160; See their <a href=\"http://www.spirescentre.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">web site</a> for further details.<br></li><li><b>Arbourthorne &amp; Norfolk Park Community Wellbeing</b>&#160;runs activities and classes including IT see <a href=\"http://www.sheffielddirectory.org.uk/kb5/sheffield/directory/service.page?id=bbcVaho4oHg\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> for further information<br></li></ul><p><b>GLEADLESS</b></p><ul><li><b>Reach&#160;</b>run health and well being activities, a work club, community learning and offer volunteering opportunities.&#160; See their&#160;<a href=\"http://reachsouthsheffield.org.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">web site</a>&#160;for more information and timetable in Printable Resources.</li></ul><p><b>WOODHOUSE</b></p><p></p><ul><li><b>&#8203;Woodhouse and District Community Forum</b>&#160;has activities and events, a health and well-being programme and a community garden project.&#160;&#160;See their&#160;<a href=\"https://www.mywoodhouse.co.uk/index.html\" target=\"_blank\">web site</a>&#160;for more information</li></ul><p>Also see:</p><p><b>ENGLISH</b> - see<i>&#160;<a href=\"https://asylumjourney.org.uk/service/51\" target=\"\">English Language Classes (ESOL) and Online Resources for Learning English</a></i><i>&#160;</i>and&#160;<i><i><i><a href=\"https://asylumjourney.org.uk/service/801\" target=\"\">Conversation Clubs</a>&#160;</i></i></i>for information about learning english .&#160; ESOL classes and conversation clubs take place in many local areas.</p><p><b>COMMUNITY ALLOTMENTS</b> - see&#160;<a class=\"in-cell-link\" href=\"https://asylumjourney.org.uk/service/514\" target=\"_blank\">Gardening</a>&#160;for information about community allotments in this area.<span class=\"rangySelectionBoundary\">&#65279;</span><br></p><p><b>FOOD BANKS - a</b>&#160;list of Sheffield food banks by post code can be found <a href=\"http://www.sheffieldfoodbank.org.uk/food-bank-list/\" target=\"\">here</a></p><p><b>IT CLASSES&#160;</b>&#160;- classes in local areas&#160;<span>can be found </span><a href=\"http://sheffieldonline.net/free-computer-classes/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></p><p><b>LIBRARIES - a</b>&#160;list of local libraries is <a href=\"https://www.sheffield.gov.uk/home/libraries-archives/our-libraries\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></p><p>* the guide covers&#160;&#160;Woodhouse, Handsworth, Hackenthorpe, Beighton,&#160;Owlthorpe, Waterthorpe, Sothall, Mosborough,&#160;Westfield, Halfway, Park Hill, Wybourn, Granville,&#160;Manor, Norfolk Park, Arbourthorne, Gleadless, Charnock, Hemsworth and Basegreen)</p><p><br><br><br></p>",
