                      "description": "<p>City of Sanctuary is a national movement to build a culture of welcome and hospitality for refugees and asylum seekers.  It started in Sheffield and Sheffield became the UK's first 'City of Sanctuary' in 2007.</p><p>The local organisation City of Sanctuary Sheffield  builds awareness and understanding through a team of refugee and asylum seekers who give talks and interactive sessions about their experiences in schools and to faith and community groups and other organisations.  It co-ordinates the weekly multi-agency drop-in at the Victoria Hall on Wednesdays at 13:00-15:30 and advocates for asylum seekers and refugees in city wide groups.</p><p><span>City of Sanctuary Sheffield provides a range of support and practical help for asylum seekers and refugees:</span></p><p><span>- Clothes Bank</span></p><p><span>- SPRING project, supporting refugees once their claim has been approved. View their information <a href=\"https://asylumjourney.org.uk/provider/2391\" target=\"\">here</a></span></p><p><span>- Welcome project, welcoming new arrivals to the city</span></p><p><span>- Health Access for Refugees Project</span></p><p>The sanctuary Building is:&#160;37-39 Chapel Walk, Sheffield City Centre, Sheffield S1 2PD . And is open on Tuesday and Thursday afternoons for a social drop in<br></p>",
