          "description": "<p><b>Sheffield Rape and Sexual Abuse Centre</b> offers confidential helpline support as well as counselling and advice on giving support to others who have been raped or sexually abused.  They also offer practical help and emotional support from an Independent Sexual Violence Advisor (ISVA).&#160; details of how to contact them are<a href=\"https://www.sheffieldmentalhealth.co.uk/support/sheffield-rape-and-sexual-abuse-centre-srasac/\" target=\"_blank\"> here</a>.&#160;&#160;&#160;For those who are not ready to talk there are useful resources <a href=\"https://www.sheffieldrapecrisis.org.uk/resources\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> .</p><p><b>South Yorkshire Sexual Assault Referral Centre (SARC) </b>is a safe place where victims attend, with or without the need for Police assistance.&#160; It enables victims to obtain advice, have forensic samples taken, receive medical care and be offered ongoing support.&#160; SARC services are available to anyone of any age.&#160; &#160;People who have experienced rape or sexual assault but do not want police involvement may &#8220;self refer&#8221; to the service - see details <a href=\"https://www.hackenthorpelodge.org/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></p><p><b>Vida </b>provide the following domestic abuse services:-&#160;</p><ul><li>Eva Women's Therapy Service ~ specialist counselling and therapy service for women affected by domestic and sexual abuse</li><li>Eva Women's Group ~ fortnightly women's support group- Juno 'Parenting After Abuse ~ 8 week groupwork programme for mothers affected by domestic abuse&#160;</li></ul><div>Further details in Printable Resources</div><p><b>Women Against Rape&#160;</b><span>have a self help guide&#160;</span><a href=\"http://womenagainstrape.net/resource/self-help-guide-survivors-rape-and-sexual-assault\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>&#160;<span>and also in Printable Resources</span></p><p><br></p>",
