          "id": 721,
          "name": "Support for Victims of Torture",
          "description": "<p><b>Freedom From Torture </b>&#160;are a UK organisation that provide therapy and medical evidence to torture survivors living in the UK and protect and promote torture survivors' rights.  They provide rehabilitation programmes including  Individual counselling and group counselling sessions including creative therapies e.g drama/music and psychotherapy .  Referrals can be made <a href=\"http://freedomfromtorture.org/page/make_a_referral\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>&#160;</p><p><b>Redress</b> is an organisation&#160;seeking justice and reparation for survivors of torture - see <a href=\"https://redress.org/help-for-survivors/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> for the services they offer.&#160; Their Torture Survivor's Handbook is in Printable Resources</p><p>Victims of torture have similar mental healthcare needs as those who suffer from post-traumatic stress disorder and therefore signposting towards self-help materials is beneficial.&#160;See&#160;<a target=\"\"><b><i></i></b></a><b><i><a href=\"https://asylumjourney.org.uk/service/871\" target=\"\">Mental Health Care</a></i></b> for more information on the support available.</p>",
