          "name": "Conversation Clubs",
          "description": "<p><b>COVID-19 UPDATE 24.08.20</b></p><p></p><div><p dir=\"ltr\"><b>Sheffield Conversation Club&#160;</b></p><p dir=\"ltr\">For those who want to meet face-to-face (outdoors observing social distancing),&#160;Conversation Club is meeting every Friday at 13:00 at Sheffield Botanical Gardens.&#160;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">The session includes an English class at 2pm for an hour (for those who want to).&#160;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">Join for friendly, informal conversation. Children are welcome too.&#160;</p><ol><ol><ol><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\">Send enquiries to Brian Helsdon <a href=\"tel:01142685333\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">0114 268 5333</a> / 07826 747565&#160;<a href=\"mailto:brian.helsdon@conversationclub.org.uk\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">brian.helsdon@conversationclub.org.uk</a>&#160;or&#160;Christine Barltrop 07890 992346</p></li></ol></ol></ol></div><p><b><br></b></p><p><b>SAVTE</b><span>&#160;have a range of online Conversation Groups taking place during the week, if you would like to join or refer someone, contact either Kerry at&#160;</span><a href=\"mailto:kerry@savte.org.uk\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">kerry@savte.org.uk</a><span>&#160;or Nuhu at&#160;</span><a href=\"mailto:nuhu@savte.org.uk\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">nuhu@savte.org.uk</a><br></p><p><br></p><p><br><br><br></p><p>There are&#160; many Conversation Clubs which&#160;offer a chance for asylum seekers and refugees to meet volunteers from the city and practice their English&#160;in an informal setting.&#160; &#160;Some conversation clubs are for women only.</p><p>The full list of conversation clubs is in Printable Resources as well as posters for individual conversation clubs where available. It is advisable to ring beforehand to check whether there are places available.</p><p>The main providers of conversation clubs are:-</p><ul><li><b>SAVTE </b>provide ESOL classes and conversation classes across Sheffield (including <br>Burngreave - women only,&#160;Sharrow, Fir Vale, Netherthorpe,) see their website for contact details and timings&#160;<a href=\"http://savte.org.uk/groups-near-you/\" target=\"\">here</a>.</li><li><b>Sheffield Conversation Club</b>&#160; run conversation clubs in central Sheffield and Pitsmoor including at the Victoria Hall drop in on Wednesday afternoons. See Conversation Club printable resource for times.<br></li></ul><p>Other providers are</p><ul><li><b>Zest</b> (Upperthorpe, Central Sheffield)</li><li><b>Learn for Life </b>provide ESOL classes and a conversation club at their premises on London Rd (Central Sheffield)</li><li><b>Darnall Wellbeing</b>(East Sheffield)<br></li><li><b>City Church Conversation Club</b> <b></b>(Firth Park - North-East Sheffield)</li><li><b>Terminus Initiative </b>(Women only - Lowedges - South Sheffield)<br></li><li><b>Reach</b> (Women only -Gleadless - South Sheffield)</li></ul><p>See also&#160;<i><a href=\"https://asylumjourney.org.uk/service/51\" target=\"\">English Language Classes (ESOL) and Online Resources for Learning English</a></i><br></p><p></p>",
          "event": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>For those who want to meet face-to-face (outdoors observing social distancing),</span><span><span>&#160;</span></span><span>Conversation Club is meeting every Friday at 13:00 at Weston Park by the steps to the side of the museum.&#160;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>The session includes an English class at 2pm for an hour (for those who want to).&#160;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Join for friendly, informal conversation. Children are welcome too.&#160;</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>",
