          "id": 911,
          "name": "Free School Meals",
          "description": "<p><b>Covid-19 Update 20.07.20</b></p><p>If you are in receipt of free school meals for your children you will benefit from the Healthy Holidays Project.&#160;</p><p>You will receive: a weekly Healthy Holidays Activity Guide printed each Monday in the Sheffield Star;</p><p>a range of activities (hopefully some face-to-face if at all possible, which will hopefully include lunch as part of what can be provided) and activity packs;</p><p>Sheffield Healthy Hampers &#8211; a weekly box containing a family make-and-eat activity, including ingredients, recipes and other exciting extras.&#160;</p><p>Please contact the New Beginning Project on 0114 2536655 Or email refugee@vas.org.uk to be included.</p><p><br></p><p><b>Covid-19 Update 07.04.20- Free School Meals</b></p><p>The Department of Education has confirmed, in its lawyers&#8217; response to a judicial review pre-action letter, that free school meal provision will be extended to families:</p><ul type=\"disc\"><li>Reliant on section 4 support</li><li>Granted leave to remain as &#8216;Zambrano carers&#8217;</li><li>Granted leave to remain under Article 8 ECHR</li><li>Supported under section 17 Children Act 1989 and who have &#8216;no recourse to public funds&#8217;.</li></ul><p><b>Update - 28.04.20</b><br></p><p><b><a href=\"https://www.project17.org.uk/resources/guide-to-accessing-support/free-school-meals-during-the-covid-19-pandemic/\" target=\"\">Project 17 </a></b><span>have produced an extremely useful factsheet which explains how families in the categories above can now&#160; apply for free school meals, including evidence requirements. This is available in printable resources. Project 17 have also produced a template letter that can be used by families to apply for free school meals, this is also in printable resources. It is recommended that families approach their school but the Local Authority can also be approached <a href=\"https://www.sheffield.gov.uk/schoolmeals\" target=\"\">here</a>.<br><br></span></p><p><b><br></b></p><p><br></p><p>Children may be eligible for free school meals.&#160; Families should talk to the school and ask the staff there to help them apply, if they are eligible.&#160; Families supported by the Home Office while they await a decision will need to show their NASS number.&#160; Refugee families on benefits will need to show their National Insurance number.</p><p>More advice about free school meals is available on the Council website <a href=\"https://www.sheffield.gov.uk/home/schools-childcare/school-meals.html\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></p>",
