                      "id": 2721,
                      "name": "Covid-19 Migrant Support Group",
                      "description": "<div><p><span lang=\"en-US\"><b>The Virtual Sanctuary</b></span>&#160;</p></div><div><div><p><span lang=\"en-US\">The Virtual Sanctuary has a number of services which</span><span lang=\"en-US\"><span>&#160;remain open and accessible to people seeking sanctuary (and those working with them) who are<span lang=\"en-US\"><span><span>&#160;struggling to&#160;</span></span><span lang=\"en-US\">find support in their communities or from other groups:</span></span></span></span></p></div><ul><li><p><span lang=\"en-US\"><b>The<span>&#160;</span></b></span><span lang=\"en-US\"><b>M</b></span><span lang=\"en-US\"><b>igrant Covid19 Support Group</b></span><span lang=\"en-US\"><b><span>&#160;-&#160;</span></b></span><span lang=\"en-US\">Provides mutual aid style support for refugees and asylum seekers in Sheffield staffed by experienced volunteers</span><span>&#160;(jan.thompson@sheffield.cityofsanctuary.org)</span></p></li><li><p><span lang=\"en-US\"><b>The Connections Team</b></span><span lang=\"en-US\"><b><span>&#160;-</span></b></span><span lang=\"en-US\"><span>&#160;Provides one to one weekly phonecalls and referral support for individuals who have found themselves isolated by the pandemic</span></span><span>&#160;(alexi.dimond@sheffield.cityofsanctuary.org)</span></p></li><li><p><span lang=\"en-US\"><b>SPRING Move-On support -<span>&#160;</span></b></span><span lang=\"en-US\">Provides move on support for refugees recently given leave to remain in the UK</span><span>&#160;(blessan@sheffield.cityofsanctuary.org)</span></p></li><li><p><span lang=\"en-US\"><b>The Asylum Journey -<span>&#160;</span></b></span><span lang=\"en-US\">Tailored, comprehensive and up to date information about services and support for people seeking Sanctuary in Sheffield</span><span>&#160;(andrew.jeffrey@sheffield.cityofsanctuary.org)</span><span lang=\"en-US\"><b></b></span></p></li><li><p><span lang=\"en-US\"><b>Homeschool project &#8211;<span>&#160;</span></b></span><span lang=\"en-US\">Provides link to a Digital Inclusion Officer (working with both us and SAVTE) who can support children, families and individuals to be dig</span><span lang=\"en-US\">itally included</span><span>&#160;(humaira@savte.org.uk)</span></p></li></ul></div><div><div><p><span lang=\"en-US\">If you want to contact The Virtual Sanctuary please use the emails above OR the phone numbers below (please note that these have changed slightly since before Christmas):</span><br></p></div></div><div><ul><li>Asylum Seeker Support &#8211; 07419348379</li><li>Refugee support - 07421313518&#8203;</li></ul></div><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>",
